question:
Trace through the execution of the recursive method `factorial(4)` step-by-step. For each call, show the call stack state, the argument value, and the return value once the base case is reached and the calls begin to return. Use the following method definition:

```java
public int factorial(int n) {
    if (n == 0) {
        return 1;
    } else {
        return n * factorial(n - 1);
    }
}
```
